      "startLine": 50,
      "endLine": 75,
      "source": "memory",
      "snippet": "Three months ago I set her up with OpenClaw to help homeschool our son. I expected her to use it for a week and forget about it. She uses it every single day. Every morning it prints custom workbooks and lesson plans. Every night it generates picture books based on what they did that day, with our family as the characters. Our son loses his mind over them. It tracks how far ahead he is on academic and emotional milestones against age benchmarks. Then it adjusts the lesson plans automatically. My wife went from \"I don't want anything to do with AI\" to running what is essentially a personalized school system. She doesn't think of it as technology. She thinks of it as her teaching assistant",
